Hi Folks, server-nginx does not build for the release-21.2.0.  We get the following error:
```12:33:55  yarn install
12:33:55  yarn install v1.22.5
12:33:55  [1/5] Resolving packages...
12:33:56  [2/5] Fetching packages...
12:33:57  error An unexpected error occurred: "https://registry.yarnpkg.com/@instabase.com/pollen/-/pollen-0.3.1.tgz: Request failed \"404 Not Found\"".
12:33:57  info If you think this is a bug, please open a bug report with the information provided in "/home/ib-build/workspace/build-service-public-server-nginx/webserver/shared/src/js/webpacked/yarn-error.log".
12:33:57  info Visit https://yarnpkg.com/en/docs/cli/install for documentation about this command.
12:33:57  make[1]: *** [Makefile:36: install-deps] Error 1
12:33:57  make[1]: Leaving directory '/home/ib-build/workspace/build-service-public-server-nginx/webserver/shared/src/js/webpacked'
12:33:57  make: *** [Makefile:36: prepare] Error 2```
I think last time we received this error, there was some token that needed to be updated.  Is it possible to cherry-pick the change in the release-21.2.0 release branch as well?  cc @Jessica @John St
Yes, I’ll do that real quick
I’m going to merge this and try to build again!  Thanks for the quick turnaround.
